    now engages at a modest size by default instead of a large one, so a
    mid-size array a user might want to cancel takes that path rather than the
    engine's uninterruptible raw-array read. Configurable via the same override.
  * A registry helper lets the keepalive thread refresh the heartbeat of the op
    running on the worker thread (a native call cannot beat for itself).

