headers it does one global swap of the bracketed-dot token back to a plain dot,
so the reconstructed tree is byte-for-byte the real source. That swap is a
no-op on a bundle that was never defanged, so the same extractor works on
either -- but the previous extractor would write broken files from a defanged
bundle, so use the updated one. To send everything as plain text, email the
defanged samql_full_source.txt and Expand-SamQL.ps1.txt (saved back with a .ps1
extension), then run the extractor.

