build 2026-06-20.102
  Downstream nodes now follow every change an upstream node makes to its
  columns -- fixing renamed/added columns not persisting into later nodes.

  The bug: a Select node's field list was seeded once and never reconciled, so
  if an upstream Select renamed a column (foo -> bar) or a Formula added one,
  the downstream Select kept its stale fields -- still referencing foo, never
  picking up bar. (The engine always chained correctly; this was the inspector
  losing track.)

  The fix: a Select's fields stay in sync with the columns actually flowing in:
    - a renamed or newly-added upstream column (e.g. a Formula's new column)
      shows up and is kept by default,
    - a column that no longer exists upstream drops out (no more "no such
      column" downstream),
    - the keep / rename / type you set on columns that survive is preserved.
  Column discovery already refreshed live for every node's inspector, so other
  nodes (Sort, Dedupe, Unique, Join, ...) already saw fresh upstream columns;
  Select was the one caching a list.

  Tests: 197 (backend 146, http 37, frontend 14). New: a Node-run unit test of
  the reconciliation logic (rename propagates, new column appears, removed
  column drops, settings preserved, order follows upstream) and a backend test
  that an upstream rename and a Formula column reach a downstream Select both in
  discovery and at run time.
