  The file loaders were already correct -- the CSV reader is RFC-4180 (handles
  quoted fields, embedded commas, doubled "" quotes, multiline cells, and keeps
  inline and leading/trailing spaces), and the Excel / JSON loaders pass native
  cell values through untouched; all loaders insert values as bound parameters,
  so a quote in the data is never a SQL hazard. The manually-entered paths had
  a gap and are fixed:

